  "prompt": "How do you know you are ready to tell your significant other you love them?",
  "response": "Deciding when to say \"I love you\" is a personal decision, but here are some signs that you might be ready:\n\n1. You feel a deep emotional connection\n- You genuinely care about their happiness\n- You can be vulnerable with them\n- You trust and respect them\n\n2. You've been together for a reasonable amount of time\n- Typically several months\n- You know each other well\n- You've experienced different situations together\n\n3. Your feelings are consistent\n- Your love isn't just a fleeting emotion\n- You've thought about it for a while\n- You're not saying it out of pressure or expectation\n\n4. You're comfortable and confident\n- You're not afraid of potential rejection\n- You're prepared for their response\n- You're saying it because you truly mean it\n\n5. You can picture a future together\n- You see them as a long-term partner\n- You're compatible and share similar values\n- You want to continue growing together\n\n6. Practical indicators\n- You think about them often\n- You want to support them through challenges\n- You prioritize their needs alongside your own\n\nRemember, there's no perfect formula. Every relationship is unique, and the right time varies for each couple. Trust your instincts and be genuine when expressing your feelings.",
